<item>
            <title>[SPR-2588] Turning on debugging causes NPE with aspects</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2588</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If log4j debugging is turned on (org.springframework=DEBUG), the container cannot load an aspect bean without getting an NPE in TransactionAttributeSourceAdvisor for the current Trails project.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The regression on this should be easy if you want to sample a project with it.  Just download Trails from trailsframework.org, generate an app from archetype and turn on log4j.logging.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you just want to look at the spring configuration, you can do that at &lt;a href=&quot;http://fisheye.codehaus.org/browse/trails/trunk/trails/trails-archetype/src/main/resources/archetype-resources/src/main/resources/applicationContext.xml?r=329&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://fisheye.codehaus.org/browse/trails/trunk/trails/trails-archetype/src/main/resources/archetype-resources/src/main/resources/applicationContext.xml?r=329&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
